data.title: Keith Varon - Can't Breathe Lyrics & Meanings
data.meta_description: Can't Breathe Lyrics & Meanings: What if time could unwind and not apply to us / What if I hadn’t fallen first, would this have worked out / So many signs not to be involved with you / So many signs to fall in love /  / (Chorus) / So what’s come over me / It’s not supposed to feel this right / What’s come over me / ‘Cause suddenly I can’t breathe /  / Are you afraid of love, are you afraid of us / ‘Cause it seems to me that we could be a possibility / Am I saying something wrong written in this song / All I ask is for a chance to seek out this romance / I know my timing’s off I’m coming on too strong / But love, it put me up to this / It’s not as if I wanted anymore complicated /  / I want you to know all you give to me / I want you to know all I’m going through /  / (Chorus)   So what’s come over me /   It’s not supposed to feel this right /   What’s come over me /   I don’t know what’s on your mind /   I can’t believe /   You and I were meant to be /   What’s come over me /   ‘Cause suddenly I can’t breathe /   (Is this what I’ve been waiting...)
data.text:
What if time could unwind and not apply to us

What if I hadn’t fallen first, would this have worked out

So many signs not to be involved with you

So many signs to fall in love

(Chorus)

So what’s come over me

It’s not supposed to feel this right

What’s come over me

‘Cause suddenly I can’t breathe

Are you afraid of love, are you afraid of us

‘Cause it seems to me that we could be a possibility

Am I saying something wrong written in this song

All I ask is for a chance to seek out this romance

I know my timing’s off I’m coming on too strong

But love, it put me up to this

It’s not as if I wanted anymore complicated

I want you to know all you give to me

I want you to know all I’m going through

(Chorus) So what’s come over me

It’s not supposed to feel this right

What’s come over me

I don’t know what’s on your mind

I can’t believe

You and I were meant to be

What’s come over me

‘Cause suddenly I can’t breathe

(Is this what I’ve been waiting...)
